<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 452px 269px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Information Requirements</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>To achieve the highest Task Team productivity we strive to be explicit in defining our <strong style="box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(95, 95, 95); font-family: &quot;Open sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Project Information Requirements</strong> and w<span style="color: rgb(95, 95, 95); font-family: &quot;Open sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">here possible in our <strong>Exchange Information Requirements&nbsp;</strong>we will define the:</span></p>
<ol>
<li>
<strong>Purpose</strong> - why we seek the information - for example to forecast replacement costs&nbsp;</li>
<li>
<strong>Content</strong> - the breakdown of information - for example the geometrical, alphanumeric and documentation required&nbsp;</li>
<li>
<strong>Form</strong> - how the information is presented - for example a schedule&nbsp;</li>
<li>
<strong>Format</strong> - how the information is encoded - for example an .xlsx file type</li>
</ol>
<p>Where Project and Exchange Information requirements are unclear it is expected that the delivery team will <strong>seek clarification</strong> by asking questions and requesting explanations through the commenting features inside Plannerly.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>